  <a href="#0" id="0">
   In this paper we explicitly consider sentence skeleton information for Machine Translation (MT.
  </a>
  <a href="#1" id="1">
   The basic idea is that we translate the key elements of the input sentence using a skeleton translation model, and then cover the remain segments using a full translation model.
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   We apply our approach to a state-of-the-art phrase-based system and demonstrate very promising BLEU improvements and TER reductions on the NIST Chinese-English MT evaluation data.
  </a>
